      "review_summary": "The PR parses `OPENCLAW_SPAWN_ALLOWLIST`/`SPAWN_ALLOWLIST` during config load and writes parsed values into `agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents` with focused parser tests.\n\nPR surface: Source +55, Tests +61. Total +116 across 3 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-reproducible: current main and `v2026.6.8` have no `SPAWN_ALLOWLIST` reader, while native and ACP spawn gates receive allowlists only from config-backed `allowAgents`. I did not run the Docker Compose scenario in this read-only review.",
